2","1208":"1208","1317":"1317","Of, Winwick, Northamptonshire, England":"Winwick, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Winwick, Northamptonshire, England":"Winwick, Northamptonshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Burford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (southwestern England and West Midlands): habitational name from Burford in Devon, Oxfordshire and Shropshire, or Burford Bridge in Surrey, so named with Old English <i>burh</i> ‘stronghold, fortified manor’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Marguerite","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Margaret  , also used in the English-speaking world, where its use has been reinforced by the fact that the name was adopted in the 19th century for a garden flower, a large cultivated variety of daisy. <i>Margaret</i> was earlier used in English as a dialect word denoting the ox-eye daisy, and the French equivalent was borrowed into English just in time to catch the vogue for deriving girls' names from vocabulary words denoting flowers.  See also  Daisy ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":9,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":18,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":53,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":84,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":109,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Marguerite Burford was born about 1206, in Winwick, Northamptonshire, England, her father, Hugh de Ferrers, was 32 and her mother, Margaret de Saye, was 26. She married George Andrews , Esq. about 1227, in Northamptonshire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"abt 1206–":"umbes 1206–Surnud","1206–Female":"1206–Surnud","1208–Male":"1208–Surnud","1194–Male":"1194–Surnud","1228–Male":"1228–Surnud","1232–1286":"1232–1286","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1182–1242":"1182–1242","Abt 1227":"umbes 1227","1242":"1242","1176":"1176","1286":"1286","1194":"1194","1182":"1182","Abt 1228":"umbes 1228","1290":"1290","1228":"1228","1206":"1206","1315":"1315","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","abt 1206":"umbes 1206","1224":"1224","1232":"1232","1208":"1208","1317":"1317","Of, Winwick, Northamptonshire, England":"Winwick, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, 